						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the Rāmaliṅgaśvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 16th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to refer a gift (details are lost) made by Vibhūti Gauraya probably to god Rāma of Vinikoṇḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
